The `disableHandle` method is a utility within a class responsible for managing and manipulating 3D transformation handles in a graphical user interface. This method specifically hides particular UI elements (e.g., posts, rings, discs) by re-parenting them to a hidden group when certain conditions are met. It is used alongside other methods like `getHandlePoint` and `drawHandleGroup` to dynamically control the visibility of these transformation controls during user interactions or state changes.

def disableHandle(self, handle):
        if handle == 'x-post':
            self.xPostGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'x-ring':
            self.xRingGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'x-disc':
            self.xDiscGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'x-scale':
            self.xScaleGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        if handle == 'y-post':
            self.yPostGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'y-ring':
            self.yRingGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'y-disc':
            self.yDiscGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'y-scale':
            self.yScaleGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        if handle == 'z-post':
            self.zPostGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'z-ring':
            self.zRingGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'z-disc':
            self.zDiscGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
        elif handle == 'z-scale':
            self.zScaleGroup.reparentTo(hidden)
